      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You can frame the \"meritocracy\" argument as a thinly veiled attempt to justify the existing power structure, where those already privileged by racism and classism are able to accumulate wealth and maintain their status through sheer force of will. By positing that wealth is solely the result of individual effort, proponents of meritocracy ignore the systemic barriers and biases that have long prevented people of color from accessing equal opportunities, education, and resources. This argument serves as a convenient smokescreen, obscuring the fact that racism and classism are deeply ingrained in the US economy and perpetuate inequality.",
